    "description": {
      "value": "<p>This technique can only be used while the user is in the Meimu no Kamae stance. The user's dance continues, and gets more complex as they enter the first dance designed to be used. All creatures within 30 feet of the user must make a will save against the technique unless they are both deaf and blind to avoid becoming stunned and dazzled for this round. A creature more than 30 feet away gains a +2 bonus to this save. Until the user's next turn, the user of this technique gains a +1 dodge bonus to defense due to hard to predict movements the dance has them perform.</p>\n\n<hr><p><b>Requires:</b> Taijutsu 6 ranks; Meimu no Kamae (t)</p>\n<p><b>Material Focus:</b> To accurately perform this technique, the user needs specially made clothes, usually equipped with whistles or bells that cause the illusion. These clothes usually have a Cost DC of 10.</p>\n",
